# Development Setup Commands

## Fix for "Ruby version is 2.6.10" Error

The error occurs because the default macOS system Ruby (v2.6) is too old for the latest CocoaPods dependencies.

### Option 1: Install via Homebrew (Recommended)
# This avoids system Ruby issues entirely
brew install cocoapods

# Link it if you have issues
brew link --overwrite cocoapods

### Option 2: Workaround for System Ruby
# If you must use gem install, try installing the older compatible dependency first:
sudo gem install securerandom -v 0.3.2
sudo gem install cocoapods

### Option 3: Update Ruby (Advanced)
# Install a modern Ruby version using Homebrew
brew install ruby
# Add to path (follow instructions from brew output)
export PATH="/opt/homebrew/opt/ruby/bin:$PATH"

## After Installation Setup
cd /Users/kalaidhamu/Desktop/KalaiDhamu/LLM/General/BankerApp_AntiGravity/ios
pod install --repo-update

## Run iOS Build
cd /Users/kalaidhamu/Desktop/KalaiDhamu/LLM/General/BankerApp_AntiGravity
flutter build ios --debug --no-codesign

## Simulator & Running
# Open Simulator
open -a Simulator

# Run on open iPhone Simulator
flutter run -d iphone

# Run on specific simulator
flutter run -d "iPhone 15 Pro"

# Run on Chrome for web testing
flutter run -d chrome --web-renderer html

# Clean and rebuild
flutter clean
flutter pub get
